definition: highway/expressway/same as 高速公路[gao1 su4 gong1 lu4]

sentences.english: The car really opened up when being on the expressway.
sentences.chinese: 一上高速路，車子就真正加快速度了。

sentences.english: To the northeast the federal highway B16 cuts through the fields.
sentences.chinese: 東北部的聯邦高速路從田野中穿過。

sentences.english: This paper proposes an approach of high?speed routing lookup based on TCAM.
sentences.chinese: 基於TCAM技術提出一個高速路由查找方案。

sentences.english: Officials say the bus veered to the right and crashed into a sound barrier wall along the highway.
sentences.chinese: 有官員說是巴士在右轉時撞上樂沿着高速路的聲障牆。

sentences.english: This expressway links the two major cities of the state.
sentences.chinese: 高速路把這個州的兩個大城市連起來了。

sentences.english: Even motorway service areas have done their bit for the toilet uprising.
sentences.chinese: 就連高速路服務區都完成了自己的廁所革命。

sentences.english: TCAM (ternary content addressable memory) is a popular device for fast routing lookup.
sentences.chinese: 是目前流行的一種高速路由查找技術。

sentences.english: Blue panels indicate that the motorway starts at the junction ahead.
sentences.chinese: 蘭色標牌指示高速路自前方路口處開始。
航道，高速路和電車軌道。

sentences.english: In their  place came commercial boulevards and highways.
sentences.chinese: 商業大道和高速路在他們那裏出現。

sentences.english: We could not even find the exit this woman had directed us to.
sentences.chinese: 卻連她指給我們的那個高速路的出口都找不到。

sentences.english: Give me a break. 7 years…North- South Expressway already built and in use by then.
sentences.chinese: 7年時間，南北線高速路都已經建好投入使用了。

sentences.english: So depending on where you go, there's some stuff, but.
sentences.chinese: 那麼取決於你要去哪兒，但是，都會有這些高速路的。

sentences.english: A multi-lane highway, empty of vehicles near Pyongyang. (David Guttenfelder/Associated Press)
sentences.chinese: 平壤附近一條空蕩的多車道高速路。

sentences.english: The overall length of the new freeway is 2387 kilometers.
sentences.chinese: 這條新高速路的總長爲2387公里。

sentences.english: A high speed routing node has been designed employing a high-performance digital cross-point switch.
sentences.chinese: 利用高性能數字交叉開關設計了高速路由結點。

definition: to travel along a route (of vehicles etc)
traffic jam/(of traffic) to get congested
